  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR 2-Advocacy towards the establishment of an independent police complaint commission/authority</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">One key outcome of engagements is the fact that all stakeholders agreed that the setting up of an IPCC is long overdue.  However, different stakeholders have different views on the type IPCC Ghana needs.  
Currently there is new government in place which is required to set up a new police council.  There is therefore the need to re-engage building on the outcomes of the previous project.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;Conduct a research into the various models of IPCC and make recommendations for the appropriate model for Ghana.  The research will be launched and used to inform advocacy on the type of structure and also engage stakeholders

&#x2022;Stakeholder engagements- There is the need to engage stakeholders especially new Minister of Interior and new Police Council and Parliament to brief them on the project and solicit buy-in and support.  Existing stakeholders also need to be re-engaged to re-ignite the advocacy    

&#x2022;	Organize a consultative meeting with stakeholders to discuss recommendations of the research and build a consensus on a suitable IPCC for Ghana</narrative>
  </description>
